graph.description:
Used to record complex human-made, or human conceived, sites, areas or landscapes. Heritage Areas can be anything from a simple prehistoric settlement site (evidenced by a few flint-working fragments) to large-scale, urban conservation areas incorporating multiple assets within a city. The use of Heritage Area or Heritage Asset will be a question of granularity.

For building complexes such as castles, prisons and airfields, Heritage Area may be used to record the footprint of the site, eg. the curtain wall and outer defences of a castle. This Heritage Area can then be used as the parent for multiple Heritage Asset records.
graph.name: Heritage Area
